<item>
            <title>[SPARK-1025] pyspark hangs when parent base file is unavailable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1025</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Working with a file in pyspark.  These steps work fine:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;mydata = sc.textFile(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;somefile&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
myfiltereddata = mydata.filter(some filter)
myfiltereddata.count()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But then I delete &quot;somefile&quot; from the file system and attempt to run&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;myfiltereddata.count()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This hangs indefinitely.  I eventually hit Ctrl-C and it displayed a stack trace.  (I will attach the output as a file.)  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It works in scala though.  If I do the same thing, the last line produces an expected error message:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;14/01/14 08:41:43 ERROR Executor: Exception in task ID 4
java.io.FileNotFoundException: File file:somefile does not exist
	at org.apache.hadoop.fs.RawLocalFileSystem.getFileStatus(RawLocalFileSystem.java:520)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
